From: Joe Yen <jyen.tech@gmail.com>
Date: 2026-06-09
Subject: [PATCH 01/10] uapi/sched: add clone3-only CLONE_NEWAGENT flag

The agent namespace is NOT created via a legacy 32-bit clone/unshare flag:
that flag space is exhausted (CSIGNAL..CLONE_IO are all claimed; CLONE_NEWTIME
0x80 took the last low bit). An early draft #define'd CLONE_NEWAGENT as
0x00000100 — which IS CLONE_VM — so every unshare(CLONE_NEWAGENT) returned
EINVAL and every kthread fork was misread as requesting a new agent NS,
hanging boot before the console came up (assay-agentns reproduces this).

Creation now goes through prctl(PR_SET_AGENT_NS) (see patch 05 / the prctl
dispatch). This patch only allocates a 64-bit clone3-only flag at
0x400000000ULL — the next free value above CLONE_INTO_CGROUP — for the
clone3(2) inheritance path. It is unreachable from unshare(2) and is NOT the
creation mechanism. The legacy CLONE_* mask is byte-identical to mainline.

Signed-off-by: Joe Yen <jyen.tech@gmail.com>
---
 include/uapi/linux/sched.h | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

--- a/include/uapi/linux/sched.h
+++ b/include/uapi/linux/sched.h
@@ -39,6 +39,8 @@
 /* Flags for the clone3() syscall. */
 #define CLONE_CLEAR_SIGHAND	0x100000000ULL /* Clear any signal handler set by the parent. */
 #define CLONE_INTO_CGROUP	0x200000000ULL /* Clone into a specific cgroup given the right permissions. */
+
+#define CLONE_NEWAGENT		0x400000000ULL	/* New agent namespace (wintermute vendor); clone3-only, NOT unshare-reachable. Userspace creates via prctl(PR_SET_AGENT_NS). */

 /*
  * cloning flags intersect with CSIGNAL so can be used with unshare and clone3
